cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Computer Architecture): The paper focuses on analyzing the power, performance, and area of NoCs in 3D-integrated and heterogeneous SoCs, which falls under the domain of computer architecture.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper deals with the analysis of NoCs in SoCs, which are a type of embedded systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the design and analysis of communication architectures in SoCs, which can be considered as a system-level problem.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with the analysis of NoCs, which are a type of distributed computing system.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of NoCs in SoCs, which falls under the domain of performance analysis.
